		<body>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>286 Nth 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St</placeName></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>Sunday</date> morning</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>February 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1856</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Robert Lyon Esqre</addressee></p>
				<p>Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I would have readily complied with<lb/> your request&#44; of which I was <sic>apprized</sic> yesterday afternoon&#44;<lb/> if the Managers of the Foster&#45;home had not <sic>preceeded</sic><lb/> your intention&#44; by resolving that the proceedings of their<lb/> first anniversary&#44; should be published&#44; in the Occident&#44;<lb/> at their expense.  I have already transmitted to<lb/> their Secretary&#44; the copy of my address&#44; and I consider<lb/> to have thereby lost any right to its disposal.</p>
				<p>You will&#44; undoubtedly approve of my conduct&#44; and rest<lb/> assured that had it been otherwise&#44; it would have afforded<lb/> me pleasure to have read my remarks in your valuable<lb/> Periodical.</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Yours respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">S. Morais</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>R. Lyon Esqre.</addressee></p>
			
